OL,6,FThe Victorian Society's annual top 10
OL,7,Flist of buildings and structures in
OL,8,Fneed of rescue ` was released on
OL,9,FWednesday ` was described as
OL,10,F"terrifying" by the society's
OL,11,Fpresident, comedian Griff Rhys Jones.
OL,12,FDesigned by architect George Sherrin
OL,13,Fand opened in 1901, a lonely Tesco
OL,14,FExpress is all that occupies the Grade
OL,15,FII-listed site today after it was
OL,16,Fforced to close in 1986 following an
OL,17,Funsuccessful campaign to save the
OL,18,Fattraction.JEach of the sites listed
OL,19,Fby The Victorian Society is Grade II-
OL,20,Flisted or above, meaning they are
OL,21,Fsubject to regulations protecting
OL,22,Ftheir historical and architectural
OL,23,Fsignificance.
